'''Tyler Grant Bindon''' (born 27 January 2005) is a New Zealand professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for {{English football updater|NottingF}} side [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]], and the [[New Zealand men's national football team|New Zealand national team]].<ref>{{Soccerway|tyler-bindon/701333|access-date=18 August 2023}}</ref>

==Early life==
Bindon was born in [[Auckland]] on 27 January 2005,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://olympic.org.nz/athletes/tyler-bindon |title=Tyler Bindon |publisher=New Zealand Olympic Committee |access-date=29 December 2025 }}</ref> to [[Jenny Bindon|Jenny]] and Grant Bindon; his mother won 77 caps for the [[New Zealand women's national football team|New Zealand women's soccer team]] and his father captained the [[New Zealand men's national volleyball team|New Zealand volleyball team]].<ref name="jenn">{{cite news |title=Bindon signs for the Royals! |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2023/august/07/tyler-bindon-joins-reading-football-club-from-los-angeles-fc/ |access-date=10 August 2023 |work=Reading FC |date=7 August 2023 |archive-date=10 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230810105534/https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2023/august/07/tyler-bindon-joins-reading-football-club-from-los-angeles-fc/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Bindon moved to California at age 12 after his mother was hired as a coach for the [[UCLA Bruins women's soccer|UCLA women's soccer team]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=ASN: Young dual national Tyler Bindon explains his decision to represent New Zealand |url=http://americansoccernow.com/articles/young-dual-national-tyler-bindon-explains-his-decision-to-represent-new-zealand |access-date=2024-07-27 |website=americansoccernow.com}}</ref>

==Club career==
Bindon began his career in New Zealand with [[East Coast Bays AFC|East Coast Bays]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Teenager Tyler Bindon lands deal with English League One club Reading! |url=https://www.friendsoffootballnz.com/2023/08/08/teenager-tyler-bindon-lands-deal-with-english-league-one-club-reading/ |access-date=23 August 2023 |work=friendsoffootballnz.com |date=8 August 2023 |archive-date=23 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230823094548/https://www.friendsoffootballnz.com/2023/08/08/teenager-tyler-bindon-lands-deal-with-english-league-one-club-reading/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Tyler Bindon signs with English League 1 club Reading FC |url=https://ecbafc.nz/latest-news/tyler-bindon-signs-with-english-league-1-club-reading-fc |access-date=23 August 2023 |work=East Coast Bays AFC |date=8 August 2023 |archive-date=23 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230823094551/https://ecbafc.nz/latest-news/tyler-bindon-signs-with-english-league-1-club-reading-fc |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 7 August 2023, Bindon signed a two-year contract with [[EFL League One]] club [[Reading F.C.|Reading]] after moving from the [[Los Angeles FC|LAFC Academy]] and featuring in four pre-season games under manager [[Rubén Sellés]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Reading sign defender Bindon from Los Angeles FC |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66432681 |access-date=10 August 2023 |work=BBC Sport |date=7 August 2023 |archive-date=10 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230810170521/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66432681 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="jenn"/> He made his professional debut the following day, in a 4–0 win at [[Millwall F.C.|Millwall]] in the [[EFL Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Reading crush Millwall for rare victory |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66368512 |access-date=10 August 2023 |work=BBC Sport |date=8 August 2023 |archive-date=9 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230809063045/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66368512 |url-status=live }}</ref> Bindon scored his first Reading goal in a 2–1 defeat to Leyton Orient on 7 October 2023.<ref>{{cite news |title=RUBÉN: "WE LOST IN A SITUATION WE COULD SOLVE… AND IT HURTS" |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2023/october/07/ruben-selles-post-match-leyton-orient-away/ |access-date=8 October 2023 |work=Reading FC |date=7 October 2023 |archive-date=13 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231013221325/https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2023/october/07/ruben-selles-post-match-leyton-orient-away/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Bindon finished runner-up in the 2023–24 [[Reading F.C. Player of the Season|Player of the Season Award]] for Reading after making 44 appearances and scoring two goals in his first season.<ref>{{cite news |title=LEWIS WING WINS PLAYER OF THE SEASON! |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2024/april/27/player-of-the-season-award-2023-24-wing/ |access-date=29 April 2024 |work=Reading FC |date=27 April 2024 |archive-date=27 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240427182929/https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2024/april/27/player-of-the-season-award-2023-24-wing/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=FLYING KIWIS – APRIL 30 |url=https://theniche-cache.com/football/2024/4/30/flying-kiwis-april-30 |access-date=1 May 2024 |work=theniche-cache.com |date=30 April 2024 |archive-date=1 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240501044619/https://theniche-cache.com/football/2024/4/30/flying-kiwis-april-30 |url-status=live }}</ref> Bindon captained Reading for the first time on 2 November 2024 against [[Fleetwood Town F.C.|Fleetwood Town]] in the first round of the [[FA Cup]] where he scored the opening goal in a 2–0 win.<ref>{{cite news |title=Team News {{!}} Your line-up for Fleetwood cup test |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2024/november/02/team-news-fleetwood-town/ |access-date=3 November 2024 |work=Reading FC |date=2 November 2024 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Report {{!}} Reading 2–0 Fleetwood Town |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2024/november/02/report-fleetwood-town/ |access-date=3 November 2024 |work=Reading FC |date=2 November 2024 }}</ref>

On 3 February 2025, Bindon signed with [[Premier League]] side [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] on a deal until June 2028 for an undisclosed transfer fee. He was immediately loaned back to Reading for the remainder of the season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nottinghamforest.co.uk/news/2025/february/03/forest-complete-signing-of-tyler-bindon/|title=Forest complete signing of Tyler Bindon|first=Nottingham Forest Football|last=Club|date=3 February 2025|website=Nottingham Forest Football Club}}</ref>

On 16 April 2025, Bindon was nominated for the 2024–25 [[EFL League One]] Young Player of the Season award alongside [[Louie Barry]] and [[Richard Kone]].<ref>{{cite web |title=EFL Awards 2025: Shortlists revealed |url=https://www.efl.com/news/2025/april/16/efl-awards-2025--shortlists-revealed/ |website=efl.com/ |publisher=English Football League |access-date=16 April 2025 |date=16 April 2025}}</ref> On 4 May 2025, Bindon was announced as Reading's Player of the Season, after scoring 3 goals in 47 appearances, helping Reading to a 7th-place finish.<ref name="auto">{{cite web |title=Tyler Bindon wins Player of the Season |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2025/may/04/player-of-the-season-24-25/ |publisher=Reading F.C. |access-date=4 May 2025 |date=4 May 2025}}</ref>

On 4 July 2025, Bindon was loaned to [[EFL Championship|Championship]] side [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]] for the 2025-26 season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sufc.co.uk/news/2025/july/04/tyler-bindon-signs/|title=Rubén secures Tyler's signature|first=Sheffield United|last=FC|date=4 July 2025|website=Sheffield United FC}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/crk6jpdy3z3o|title=Tyler Bindon: Sheffield United sign Nottingham Forest defender on loan|date=4 July 2025|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

On 20 December 2025, Bindon scored his first goal for Sheffield United in a 3–0 win over [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Sheffield United 3–0 Birmingham City: Blades cruise past 10-player Blues |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/13484400/sheffield-united-3-0-birmingham-city-blades-cruise-past-10-player-blues |website=Sky Sports |access-date=20 December 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Bindon won his first [[Cap (sport)|cap]] for the [[United States men's national under-19 soccer team|United States under-19]] team against Argentina in March 2023, having been eligible to represent the US through his American-born mother.<ref name=":0" /><ref name="jenn"/>

On 26 September 2023, Bindon was called up to the [[New Zealand men's national football team]] for the first time.<ref>{{cite web |title=Two players called up for All Whites debuts in Darren Bazeley's first squad since becoming permanent head coach |url=https://www.nzfootball.co.nz/newsarticle/133361 |website=nzfootball.co.nz |publisher=New Zealand Football |access-date=26 September 2023 |date=26 September 2023 |archive-date=26 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230926091319/https://www.nzfootball.co.nz/newsarticle/133361 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Teenage centre back Tyler Bindon named in All Whites squad for October friendlies |url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/sport/football/nz-teams/133007636/teenage-centre-back-tyler-bindon-named-in-all-whites-squad-for-october-friendlies |website=Stuff |access-date=26 September 2023 |date=26 September 2023 |archive-date=26 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230926091325/https://www.stuff.co.nz/sport/football/nz-teams/133007636/teenage-centre-back-tyler-bindon-named-in-all-whites-squad-for-october-friendlies |url-status=live }}</ref> Bindon made his debut on 13 October 2023 when he came on as a late substitute replacing [[Michael Boxall]] against the [[DR Congo national football team|Democratic Republic of Congo]].<ref>{{cite web |title=All Whites captain Chris Wood rescues draw with late penalty against DR Congo |url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/sport/football/133107655/all-whites-captain-chris-wood-rescues-draw-with-late-penalty-against-dr-congo |website=Stuff |access-date=14 October 2023 |date=14 October 2023 |archive-date=13 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231013211325/https://www.stuff.co.nz/sport/football/133107655/all-whites-captain-chris-wood-rescues-draw-with-late-penalty-against-dr-congo |url-status=live }}</ref> On 17 November 2023, Bindon made his first start for New Zealand in a friendly against [[Greece men's national football team|Greece]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Recap: All Whites suffer 2–0 loss to Greece in men's international football friendly |url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/sport/football/nz-teams/301007582/recap-all-whites-suffer-20-loss-to-greece-in-mens-international-football-friendly |website=Stuff |publisher=[[Stuff (website)|Stuff]] |access-date=27 March 2024 |date=18 November 2023 |archive-date=26 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240326231900/https://www.stuff.co.nz/sport/football/nz-teams/301007582/recap-all-whites-suffer-20-loss-to-greece-in-mens-international-football-friendly |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=All Whites vs Greece score: New Zealand go down 2–0 to Greece despite stronger second half |url=https://www.nzherald.co.nz/sport/all-whites-vs-greece-live-updates/Y7JEZUDT45FZDNXQJSC3IYHNFE/ |work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]|access-date=27 March 2024 |date=18 November 2023 |archive-date=28 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240528100219/https://www.nzherald.co.nz/sport/football/all-whites/all-whites-vs-greece-score-new-zealand-go-down-2-0-to-greece-despite-stronger-second-half/Y7JEZUDT45FZDNXQJSC3IYHNFE/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In February 2024, Bindon was nominated for the 2023 New Zealand Men's Young Player of the Year.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nzfootball.co.nz/newsarticle/137746 |title=Vote now in the New Zealand Football Awards |publisher=New Zealand Football |date=22 February 2024 |access-date=29 April 2024 |archive-date=29 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240429072647/https://www.nzfootball.co.nz/newsarticle/137746 |url-status=live }}</ref>

In July 2024 he was selected to the [[New Zealand men's national under-23 football team|New Zealand]] squad at the [[2024 Summer Olympics]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://readingfc.co.uk//news/2024/july/09/bindon-olympic-call-up/|title=Bindon becomes an Olympian!|first=Reading|last=FC|date=9 July 2024|website=Reading FC}}</ref><ref>https://www.fifa.com/en/tournaments/olympicgames/paris2024/mens/articles/tyler-bindon-new-zealand-interview</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.friendsoffootballnz.com/2024/07/23/tyler-bindons-dreams-of-olympic-glory-and-the-secret-inside-his-socks/|title=Tyler Bindon's dreams of Olympic glory ... and the secret inside his socks|date=22 July 2024|website=Friends of Football}}</ref> Bindon made his Olympic debut in the opening group game, a 2–1 win over [[Guinea national under-23 football team|Guinea]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://olympics.com/en/paris-2024/results/football/men/gpa-000200--|title=Guinea vs New Zealand – Men's Group A Match 2|access-date=27 July 2024|publisher=[[International Olympic Committee]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nzfootball.co.nz/newsarticle/143482?newsfeedId=1275622|title=Men's Olympic Team beat Guinea to start Paris 2024 campaign with a win|date=24 July 2024|access-date=27 July 2024|website=New Zealand Football}}</ref>

Bindon scored his first goal for [[New Zealand men's national football team|New Zealand]] on 15 November 2024, in a 8–1 victory over [[Vanuatu national football team|Vanuatu]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/en/news/articles/ofc-round-two-matchday-four-report|title=Ruthless New Zealand rout Vanuatu to reach third round|publisher=[[FIFA]]|date=14 November 2024|access-date=15 November 2024}}</ref>

